<i>O fathers, let's go down</i>

273
00:18:03,892 --> 00:18:07,290
<i>Let's go down, come on down</i>

274
00:18:07,492 --> 00:18:10,690
<i>O fathers, let's go down</i>

275
00:18:10,992 --> 00:18:14,990
<i>Down in the river to pray</i>

276
00:18:15,292 --> 00:18:18,990
<i>As I went down
in the river to pray</i>

277
00:18:19,192 --> 00:18:22,190
<i>Studying about that good old way</i>

278
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:25,590
<i>And who shall wear
the robe and crown</i>

279
00:18:25,792 --> 00:18:30,290
<i>Good lord, show me the way</i>

280
00:18:30,592 --> 00:18:33,790
<i>O mothers, let's go down</i>

281
00:18:33,992 --> 00:18:37,190
<i>Come on down,
don't you wanna go down ?</i>

282
00:18:37,392 --> 00:18:40,990
<i>Come on, mothers,
let's go down...</i>

283
00:18:41,192 --> 00:18:44,190
Well, I guess hard times
flush the chumps.

284
00:18:44,392 --> 00:18:46,390
Everybody's lookin' for answers.

285
00:18:50,192 --> 00:18:51,790
Where the hell's he going ?

286
00:18:52,092 --> 00:18:55,790
The Father, the Son
and the Holy Ghost.

287
00:18:56,092 --> 00:18:59,790
<i>Good Lord, show me the way</i>

288
00:18:59,992 --> 00:19:04,290
<i>O sinners, let's go down...</i>

289
00:19:04,592 --> 00:19:06,790
Well, I'll be a son of a bitch.

290
00:19:06,992 --> 00:19:08,890
Delmar's been saved.

291
00:19:09,192 --> 00:19:11,990
Well, that's it, boys.
I been redeemed.

292
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:16,290
The preacher done washed away
all my sins and transgressions.

293
00:19:16,492 --> 00:19:19,190
It's the straight and narrow
from here on out.

294
00:19:19,492 --> 00:19:21,890
And heaven everlasting's
my reward.

295
00:19:22,092 --> 00:19:25,190
Delmar, what are you on about ?
We got bigger fish to fry.

296
00:19:25,392 --> 00:19:28,290
The preacher said
all my sins is washed away,

297
00:19:28,492 --> 00:19:31,390
including that Piggly Wiggly
I knocked over in Yazoo.

298
00:19:31,592 --> 00:19:33,590
You said you was innocent of that.

299
00:19:33,792 --> 00:19:35,990
Well, I was lyin'.

300
00:19:36,192 --> 00:19:39,790
And the preacher said that
that sin's been washed away, too.

301
00:19:39,992 --> 00:19:43,190
Neither God nor man's
got nothin' on me now.

302
00:19:43,492 --> 00:19:48,190
Come on in, boys.
The water is fine.

303
00:19:53,892 --> 00:19:56,590
Come on, boy.
There, boy. Good doggy.

304
00:19:58,992 --> 00:20:02,690
All right, boys, we got the scent.

305
00:20:05,192 --> 00:20:08,790
- The preacher said it absolved us.
- For Him, not for the law.

306
00:20:08,992 --> 00:20:11,590
I gave you credit for
more brains than Delmar.

307
00:20:11,792 --> 00:20:15,690
- But witnesses seen us redeemed.
- That's not the issue, Delmar.

308
00:20:15,992 --> 00:20:19,090
Even square with the Lord,
Mississippi's hard-nosed.

309
00:20:19,292 --> 00:20:22,590
You shoulda joined us, Everett.
It couldn'a hurt none.

310
00:20:22,792 --> 00:20:26,090
Hell, it woulda washed away
the stink of that pomade.

311
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:29,790
Joining you fools in superstition ?
Thank you, anyway.

312
00:20:30,092 --> 00:20:35,190
And I like the smell of my hair,
the pleasin' odour's half the point.

313
00:20:35,392 --> 00:20:37,290
Baptism !

314
00:20:37,492 --> 00:20:39,690
You two are
dumber than a bag of hammers.

315
00:20:39,992 --> 00:20:41,790
You're my cross to bear.

316
00:20:41,992 --> 00:20:46,690
Pull over, Everett. Let's give
that coloured boy a lift.

317
00:20:52,392 --> 00:20:54,690
You folks going past Tishomingo ?

318
00:20:54,892 --> 00:20:57,690
Sure, hop in.

319
00:21:04,392 --> 00:21:06,590
How you doin', son ? Name's Everett.

320
00:21:06,892 --> 00:21:10,090
These two soggy sons of bitches
are Pete and Delmar.

321
00:21:10,392 --> 00:21:13,990
Keep your fingers away from Pete's
mouth, he ain't eaten for 13 years,

322
00:21:14,192 --> 00:21:16,390
'cept prison food and greasy horse.

323
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:20,390
Thanks for the lift, sir.
My name's Tommy. Tommy Johnson.

324
00:21:20,692 --> 00:21:22,490
How you doin', Tommy ?

325
00:21:22,692 --> 00:21:25,590
Say, I haven't seen a house
out here for miles.

326
00:21:25,892 --> 00:21:28,290
Why are you
out in the middle of nowhere ?

327
00:21:28,492 --> 00:21:31,090
I had to be at that crossroads
last midnight.

328
00:21:31,392 --> 00:21:33,190
Sell my soul to the devil.

329
00:21:33,392 --> 00:21:35,790
Ain't it a small world,
spiritually speakin' ?

330
00:21:35,992 --> 00:21:39,990
Pete and Delmar just been saved.
I'm the only one still unaffiliated.

331
00:21:40,292 --> 00:21:42,290
It's no laughin' matter.

332
00:21:42,592 --> 00:21:44,290
What'd the devil give you for it ?

333
00:21:44,492 --> 00:21:47,790
Well, he taught me to play
this here guitar real good.

334
00:21:47,992 --> 00:21:52,090
Oh, son, for that you traded
your everlasting soul ?

335
00:21:52,392 --> 00:21:53,790
Well, I wasn't usin' it.

336
00:21:53,992 --> 00:21:57,990
I've always wondered,
what's the devil look like ?

337
00:21:58,192 --> 00:22:01,590
Well, there are all manner
of lesser imps and demons,

338
00:22:01,792 --> 00:22:05,290
but Satan hisself is red and scaly
with a bifurcated tail,

339
00:22:05,592 --> 00:22:08,890
- and he carries a hayfork.
- Oh, no. No, sir.

340
00:22:09,092 --> 00:22:12,390
He's white.
As white as you folks.

341
00:22:12,592 --> 00:22:15,390
With empty eyes
and a big, hollow voice.

342
00:22:15,592 --> 00:22:19,190
He travelled around
with a mean old hound, that's right.

343
00:22:19,392 --> 00:22:21,290
He told you to go to Tishomingo ?

344
00:22:21,492 --> 00:22:24,190
Well, no, sir.
Why, that was my idea.

345
00:22:24,492 --> 00:22:26,190
I heard there's a man there,

346
00:22:26,492 --> 00:22:28,690
pays folks money
to sing into his can.

347
00:22:28,992 --> 00:22:32,690
They say he pays extra
if'n you play real good.

348
00:22:32,892 --> 00:22:34,690
Tishomingo, huh ?

349
00:22:34,892 --> 00:22:36,390
How much he pay ?

350
00:22:52,192 --> 00:22:56,690
All right, boys, follow my lead.

351
00:23:00,592 --> 00:23:02,890
Hello ?

352
00:23:03,192 --> 00:23:07,590
- Who's the honcho here ?
- I am. Who are you ?

353
00:23:07,792 --> 00:23:12,090
Well, sir, I'm Jordan Rivers,
and these are the Soggy Bottom Boys,

354
00:23:12,292 --> 00:23:14,190
out of Cottonillia, Mississippi.

355
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:16,690
Songs of salvation to salve the soul.

356
00:23:16,992 --> 00:23:20,590
Uh, we hear that you pay good money
to sing into a can.

357
00:23:20,792 --> 00:23:23,990
Well, that all depends.
You boys do Negro songs ?

358
00:23:24,192 --> 00:23:28,890
Um... Well, uh, sir, we are Negroes.

359
00:23:29,092 --> 00:23:32,990
All except for our accomp... accomp...
the fella that plays the guitar.

360
00:23:33,192 --> 00:23:35,290
Yeah, well,
I don't record Negro songs.

361
00:23:35,592 --> 00:23:38,790
No, I'm lookin' for
some old-timey material.

362
00:23:39,092 --> 00:23:40,990
People can't seem to get enough

363
00:23:41,192 --> 00:23:44,490
since we started broadcasting it
on the Pappy O'Daniel Flour Hour,

364
00:23:44,792 --> 00:23:46,890
so thank you for stopping by, but...

365
00:23:47,192 --> 00:23:51,790
Sir, the Soggy Bottom Boys have been
steeped in old-timey material.

366
00:23:51,992 --> 00:23:54,590
- Heck, we're silly with it.
- That's right.

367
00:23:54,892 --> 00:23:56,790
Right. We ain't really Negroes.

368
00:23:57,092 --> 00:23:59,090
All except for our accompanist.

369
00:24:01,592 --> 00:24:05,690
<i>I am a man</i>

370
00:24:05,892 --> 00:24:08,590
<i>Of constant sorrow</i>

371
00:24:08,792 --> 00:24:14,590
<i>I've seen trouble all my days</i>

372
00:24:14,792 --> 00:24:18,990
<i>I bid farewell</i>

373
00:24:19,292 --> 00:24:21,690
<i>To old Kentucky</i>

374
00:24:21,992 --> 00:24:24,190
<i>The place where I</i>

375
00:24:24,392 --> 00:24:26,990
<i>Was born and raised</i>

376
00:24:27,192 --> 00:24:29,890
<i>The place where he</i>

377
00:24:30,192 --> 00:24:33,390
<i>Was born and raised</i>

378
00:24:33,592 --> 00:24:37,790
<i>For six long years</i>

379
00:24:38,092 --> 00:24:40,490
<i>I've been in trouble</i>

380
00:24:40,792 --> 00:24:43,290
<i>No pleasure here</i>

381
00:24:43,592 --> 00:24:46,790
<i>On Earth I found</i>

382
00:24:46,992 --> 00:24:51,090
<i>For in this world</i>

383
00:24:51,292 --> 00:24:53,390
<i>I'm bound to ramble</i>

384
00:24:53,592 --> 00:24:56,490
<i>I have no friends</i>

385
00:24:56,692 --> 00:24:59,190
<i>To help me now</i>

386
00:24:59,492 --> 00:25:01,890
<i>He has no friends</i>

387
00:25:02,192 --> 00:25:05,490
<i>To help him now</i>

388
00:25:05,792 --> 00:25:09,990
<i>Maybe your friends think</i>

389
00:25:10,292 --> 00:25:12,690
<i>I'm just a stranger</i>

390
00:25:12,992 --> 00:25:15,290
<i>My face you never</i>

391
00:25:15,592 --> 00:25:16,790
<i>Will see no more</i>

392
00:25:19,192 --> 00:25:23,790
<i>But there is one promise</i>

393
00:25:24,092 --> 00:25:25,990
<i>That is given</i>

394
00:25:26,192 --> 00:25:28,690
<i>I'll meet you on</i>

395
00:25:28,992 --> 00:25:31,390
<i>God's golden shore</i>

396
00:25:31,692 --> 00:25:34,190
<i>He'll meet you on</i>

397
00:25:34,392 --> 00:25:39,190
<i>God's golden shore</i>

398
00:25:40,492 --> 00:25:43,890
Whoo ! Hot damn, son !
You did sell your soul to the devil !

399
00:25:45,592 --> 00:25:49,290
Boy, that was some mighty fine
a-pickin' and a-singin'.

400
00:25:49,492 --> 00:25:50,790
I'll tell you what.

401
00:25:50,992 --> 00:25:53,190
Ahem. You come on
in here, you...

402
00:25:53,392 --> 00:25:57,690
you sign these papers here,
I'm gonna give you $10 apiece.

403
00:25:57,992 --> 00:26:03,890
Uh, OK, sir, but Mert and...
Aloysious'll have to sign x's.

404
00:26:04,192 --> 00:26:07,990
- Only four of us can write.
- That'd be fine.

405
00:26:10,792 --> 00:26:13,990
Hey, mister, I don't mean
to tell tales out of school,

406
00:26:14,192 --> 00:26:17,890
but there's a fella in there'll pay
you $10 if you sing into his can.

407
00:26:18,192 --> 00:26:21,090
I'm not hear to make a record,
you dumb cracker.

408
00:26:21,292 --> 00:26:23,090
They broadcast me on the radio.

409
00:26:23,292 --> 00:26:26,090
That's Governor Menelaus
"Pappy" O'Daniel.

410
00:26:26,392 --> 00:26:30,290
He'd sure like it if you ate his
farina and voted him a second term.

411
00:26:30,592 --> 00:26:33,090
- Finest in Mississippi.
- In any state.

412
00:26:33,392 --> 00:26:35,490
Lord, yes. Every parish.

413
00:26:35,692 --> 00:26:38,390
Ain't you gonna
press the flesh, Pappy ?

414
00:26:38,592 --> 00:26:41,690
I'll press your flesh,
you dim-witted son'bitch.

415
00:26:41,892 --> 00:26:45,590
Don't tell me how to court the
electorate. We ain't one-at-a-timin'.

416
00:26:45,892 --> 00:26:47,490
We're mass communicatin' !

417
00:26:47,692 --> 00:26:50,190
Oh, yes, that's a powerful new force.

418
00:26:50,392 --> 00:26:51,790
Shake a leg, Junior.

419
00:26:51,992 --> 00:26:54,290
Thank God your mammy died
givin' birth,

420
00:26:54,492 --> 00:26:55,990
she'd have died of shame.

421
00:26:56,192 --> 00:26:58,090
Well, hi there ! How you doin' ?

422
00:26:59,992 --> 00:27:05,390
<i>Hard time yearnin'
where you go</i>

423
00:27:05,592 --> 00:27:10,990
<i>Times is harder
than ever been before</i>

424
00:27:15,992 --> 00:27:18,990
<i>And the people are driftin'</i>

425
00:27:19,192 --> 00:27:21,590
<i>From door to door</i>

426
00:27:21,892 --> 00:27:23,190
<i>Can't find no heaven</i>

427
00:27:23,392 --> 00:27:26,590
<i>I don't care where they go</i>

428
00:27:36,792 --> 00:27:39,190
<i>Say you had money</i>

429
00:27:39,392 --> 00:27:41,790
<i>You better be sure</i>

430
00:27:41,992 --> 00:27:43,790
<i>These hard times will drive you</i>

431
00:27:43,992 --> 00:27:46,790
<i>From door to door</i>

432
00:27:58,092 --> 00:28:00,390
Let's bed down here for the night.

433
00:28:00,592 --> 00:28:04,090
Yeah, it stinks in that old barn.

434
00:28:04,392 --> 00:28:05,690
Suits me.

435
00:28:05,992 --> 00:28:11,590
Pretty soon it'll be nothin' but
featherbeds and silk sheets.

436
00:28:14,592 --> 00:28:16,290
A million dollars.

437
00:28:16,592 --> 00:28:18,390
Million point two.

438
00:28:18,692 --> 00:28:23,190
- 500,000 each.
- 400, Delmar.

439
00:28:23,392 --> 00:28:29,790
Pete, what are you gonna do
with your share of the treasure ?

440
00:28:30,092 --> 00:28:32,490
Go out west somewhere.

441
00:28:32,692 --> 00:28:36,190
Open a fine restaurant.

442
00:28:36,292 --> 00:28:39,590
I'm gonna be the maitre d'.

443
00:28:39,792 --> 00:28:42,390
Greet all the swells.

444
00:28:42,592 --> 00:28:45,790
Go to work every day
in a bow tie,

445
00:28:45,992 --> 00:28:47,990
tuxedo.

446
00:28:48,192 --> 00:28:51,590
And all the staff
say "yes, sir" and...

447
00:28:51,792 --> 00:28:53,090
"no, sir"...

448
00:28:53,292 --> 00:28:56,590
and "in a jiffy, Pete".

449
00:28:56,892 --> 00:29:00,790
And all my meals for free.

450
00:29:03,592 --> 00:29:05,390
What about you, Delmar,

451
00:29:05,592 --> 00:29:08,690
what are you gonna do
with your share of that dough ?

452
00:29:08,992 --> 00:29:12,490
I'm gonna visit them
foreclosin' son of a guns

453
00:29:12,692 --> 00:29:16,190
down at the Indianola
Savings and Loan.

454
00:29:16,392 --> 00:29:22,190
Slap that money on the barrel head
and buy back the family farm.

455
00:29:22,392 --> 00:29:26,790
You ain't no kind of man
if you ain't got land.

456
00:29:26,992 --> 00:29:28,790
What about you, Everett ?

457
00:29:29,092 --> 00:29:32,690
What you have in mind
when you stole it in the first place ?

458
00:29:32,992 --> 00:29:38,990
Ahem. I... didn't have no plan.

459
00:29:39,192 --> 00:29:41,990
Well, that hardly sounds like you.

460
00:29:42,292 --> 00:29:45,390
All right, boys !
It's the authorities !

461
00:29:45,592 --> 00:29:48,090
Your situation
is purty nigh hopeless !

462
00:29:48,292 --> 00:29:50,590
Damn, they found our car.

463
00:29:50,792 --> 00:29:53,790
We ain't got the time
and nary the inclination

464
00:29:54,092 --> 00:29:56,390
to chat with you boys any further.

465
00:29:56,692 --> 00:29:58,690
Damn, we got to skedaddle.

466
00:29:58,892 --> 00:30:02,690
I left my pomade in the car.
Maybe I can creep up.

467
00:30:02,992 --> 00:30:07,090
Don't be a fool, Everett.
We got to R-U-N-N-O-F-T.

468
00:30:07,392 --> 00:30:09,190
Where's Tommy ?

469
00:30:09,392 --> 00:30:14,390
Already lit out,
scared out of his wits.

470
00:30:15,492 --> 00:30:18,290
Let's go !

471
00:30:18,492 --> 00:30:20,390
Well, hell, it ain't square one.

472
00:30:20,592 --> 00:30:24,490
Ain't no one gonna pick up three
filthy, unshaved hitchhikers.

473
00:30:24,792 --> 00:30:28,590
And one of them a know-it-all
who can't keep his trap shut.

474
00:30:28,792 --> 00:30:32,890
The rancour reflected in that remark
I won't dignify with comment.

475
00:30:33,192 --> 00:30:37,190
But I'll address your general
attitude of hopeless negativism.

476
00:30:37,392 --> 00:30:40,090
Consider the lilies
of the goddam field.

477
00:30:40,292 --> 00:30:43,190
Or, hell, look at Delmar
